{
  "texts": [
    "Current research on elevator fault diagnosis is still mainly focused on the use of real elevator data.",
    "QIU C et al.",
    "4 proposed an elevator fault diagnosis method based on Recursive Feature Elimination (RFE)-SMOTE-Tomek and IAO-XGBoost to address the sample imbalance and hyper-parameter rectification problems of the XGBoost model.",
    "This research can better predict potential faults and take preventive maintenance measures so as to extend the service life of elevators and improve their reliability; ZHAO M et al.",
    "19 proposed and developed a deep residual contraction network model inspired by the residual blocks in the deep learning model ResNet."
  ]
}